The functional response describes how a consumer’s resource consumption rate varies as a function of resource abundance45. This concept, widely used in ecological modeling, provides insights into how fluctuations in resource availability influence both consumer dynamics and resource populations. Building on previous studies, we parameterise the functional response in terms of the body size of the interacting species10,23–25. Specifically, we employ the following expression:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
