The question arises as to whether the pest could lead to the extinction of the plant. If so, what relationships between the body sizes of the species involved would allow this to occur? Specifically, we want to understand under what conditions body sizes must align for the species to persist in the ecosystem. Theoretically, this involves determining the necessary conditions for x(t) to be greater than zero, where x represents the densities of the species involved. Mathematically, this is expressed as: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
