On the other hand, the persistence of the pest (C) is determined by the interaction between top-down controls (predation, P) and bottom-up controls (resource availability and consumption, R). This model explicitly incorporates the dependence of body sizes in both trophic regulation mechanisms, providing a framework to explore their influence on system dynamics. This relationship can be analyzed through the following inequality:7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
