To evaluate the indirect effects of biological control on plant abundance, we use the concept of trophic cascade, defined as the intensity of the indirect interaction between species. To model and quantify this phenomenon, we adopt the definition proposed by Borer et al.51,52. Since body size influences trophic interactions, it is reasonable to assume that the magnitude of the trophic cascade depends on this factor, as suggested by Delong40. This indicator is expressed as a ratio, where the numerator represents the abundance in the presence of biological control, while the denominator corresponds to the abundance in its absence. The relationship is presented in the following equation:19\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} \mathscr {T}[m_{R},m_{C},m_{P}] = \frac{R_1^*}{R_{*}}. \end{aligned}$$\end{document}The conditions for Eq. (19) are to be defined and positive for ensuring the viability of the trophic cascade intensity model. These conditions are expressed as follows:20\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} H_{0}(m_{C},m_{R})e_{C} \cdot \left\{ \frac{m_{R}}{m_{C}} \right\} \cdot \Phi (m_{C},m_{R})> \delta _{C} \cdot m_{C}^{\alpha _{C}-1} \quad \text {,} \quad K \cdot m_{R}^{\gamma _{R}} > H_{0}(m_{C},m_{R}), \end{aligned}$$\end{document}and21\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} \left[ H_{0}(m_{C},m_{R}) - K \cdot m_{R}^{\gamma _{R}} \right] ^{2} \ge 4\cdot K\cdot m_{R}^{\gamma _{R}}\cdot H_{0}(m_{C},m_{R}) \cdot \left[ \frac{\Phi (m_{C},m_{R})\cdot C_{*}}{r\cdot m_{R}^{\alpha _{R}}} - 1 \right] . \end{aligned}$$\end{document}These inequalities ensure the positivity of the model, indicating that this mathematical object has a coherent ecological interpretation. By fixing the body size of the pest at \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
