				\begin{document}$$m_P$$\end{document} where the effect is more intense, while the lighter areas indicate a lesser effect. No local maxima or minima are observed in the graph, although these may arise if other mathematical expressions with an appropriate ecological interpretation are incorporated into the parameters. This model is useful as a useful tool for developing management strategies focused on the body size of biological control and its impact on plants.Fig. 7
